               <head>Naqshbandi Sufi treatise</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Hidāyat al-ṭālibīn by Abū Saʿīd Mujaddidī Naqshbandīyah Aḥmadīyah</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1019-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7049">Abū Saʿīd Mujaddidī Naqshbandīyah Aḥmadīyah</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22186">Hidāyat al-ṭālibīn</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on Mujaddidī Naqshbandī Sufism for novices, expanding on the writings of the <persName key="viaf_32839461" role="ant">Imām Rabbānī Mujaddid-i Alf-i S̲ānī</persName>
                           <persName key="viaf_32839461" role="ant">Shaykh Aḥmad Fārūqī Sarhindī</persName> (d. 1034/1624), by an author who appears to have been an adherent of his teachings, named at the beginning Abū Saʿīd Mujaddidī and in the colophon Abū Saʿīd Naqshbandīyah Aḥmadīyah. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The title and author’s name is stated in the colophon alone. 
</p>
                        <p>The work was begun in 1225/1810 at <placeName>Delhi</placeName>, and completed around 1233/1818. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into five faṣl. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 48r): completed Friday, 23 Rajab 1249/6 December 1833. </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
